	<Title>
		Healthy fast food? Yep, it&apos;s possible
	</Title>
	<Body>
		&lt;p&gt;You can eat healthy away from home, even at restaurants with drive-throughs. Try these five tips: 1. Keep portions small. Choose a regular-sized hamburger and a small serving of french fries. Or order a kid&apos;s meal. 2. Choose grilled items, such as turkey or chicken breast. 3. Opt for an entree salad with fat-free or low-fat dressing. 4. Select a healthy side dish, such as fruit or a baked potato. 5. Skip shakes and ice-cream drinks, as well as high-calorie condiments, such as special dressings, tartar sauce and mayonnaise.&lt;/p&gt;
	</Body>
